<%= render 'breadcrumbs', trail: { '/' => 'Home' }, current: 'Help' %>

<div class="govuk-grid-row">
  <div class="govuk-grid-column-one-half">
    <h1 class="govuk-heading-l govuk-!-margin-bottom-6">
      Missing cases
    </h1>

    <h2 class="govuk-heading-m govuk-!-margin-bottom-2">
      Information missing on NOMIS or NDelius
    </h2>
    <p>
      Make sure information about the case has been entered correctly on NOMIS.
      For example, this might include sentence calculation dates.
    </p>
    <p>
      Also check if the case is listed on
      <a class="govuk-link govuk-link--no-visited-state" href="#">Add missing details</a>.
      If it is, you will need to manually add some information from NDelius before it can be displayed.
    </p>

    <h2 class="govuk-heading-m govuk-!-margin-bottom-2">
      Check the case needs a POM
    </h2>
    <p>Cases that do not need a POM will not be displayed. This might be because someone:</p>
    <p></p>
    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
      <li>is on remand</li>
      <li>is under 18</li>
      <li>is involved in a civil case</li>
      <li>does not have an earliest release date or parole hearing date in NOMIS</li>
    </ul>
    <p></p>

    <h2 class="govuk-heading-m govuk-!-margin-bottom-2">
      Life sentences
    </h2>
    <p>
      If someone on a life sentence is showing as a determinate case, you need to make the case active on NOMIS.
    </p>

    <h2 class="govuk-heading-m govuk-!-margin-bottom-2">
      If you still need help
    </h2>
    <p>
      <a class="govuk-link govuk-link--no-visited-state" href="<%= service_now_external_url %>">
        Tell us about the problem you are having
      </a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
